Reasoning: The paper deals with the effect of oscillator phase noise on the performance of Massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of time-reversal maximum-ratio combining reception strategy suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The analysis of the impact of phase noise on the effective channel and the number of scheduled users indicates a possible connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the use of Massive MIMO technology in the study suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
